-- TransCredit Valued at $1.8 Billion Before Sale to VTB, Vedomosti Reports
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2010-09-28T04:06:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/transcredit-valued-at-1-8-billion-before-sale-to-vtb-vedomosti-reports.html
OAO TransCreditBank , a lender
controlled by  OAO Russian Railways , may be valued at as much as
55 billion rubles ($1.8 billion) before the sale of a stake to
state-run  VTB Group , Vedomosti  reported .  TransCredit may be valued at 2.2 times its capital and the
decision needs to be approved at a Russian Railways board
meeting scheduled for Oct. 12, the newspaper said, citing
unidentified people close to the railroad monopoly.  To contact the reporters on this story:
 Ilya Khrennikov  in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net . 